  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p>\n<p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p>\n<p>Skim through these steps</p>\n<p>Wash your fruit and veg</p>\n<p>Note: equipment and pan sizes vary. Ensure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-fiery-chicken-arrabbiata-fusilli/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced chicken</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 2 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-fiery-chicken-arrabbiata-fusilli/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>quick cook fusilli</strong> to a pot <span class=\"text-highlight\">with</span> plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the<strong> fusilli</strong> for just 2 min (it will keep cooking in the sauce later!)</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>fusilli</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-fiery-chicken-arrabbiata-fusilli/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>garlic paste</strong> to the pan with the chicken and cook for 10 sec</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and crumble in the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and give everything a good mix up until fully combined</p>\n<p>Cook for 2 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-fiery-chicken-arrabbiata-fusilli/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>basil </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-fiery-chicken-arrabbiata-fusilli/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>baby leaf spinach</strong> to the pan with the chicken and cook for 1 min, stirring until beginning to wilt</p>\n<p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> chicken &amp; spinach arrabbiata sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-fiery-chicken-arrabbiata-fusilli/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained fusilli</strong> to the <strong>chicken &amp; spinach arrabbiata sauce</strong> with a small splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Cook for 1 min further or until the chicken is cooked through </p>\n<p>Note: please ensure you cook your chicken thoroughly (until there's no pink meat and it's piping hot!) as cooking equipment varies</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-fiery-chicken-arrabbiata-fusilli/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Set the <strong>chicken &amp; spinach arrabbiata fusilli</strong> in the centre of the table, ready to share</p>\n<p>Top with the<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and <strong>chopped basil</strong> and let everyone dig in</p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
